docs.lead_paragraph: His Imperial Highness Prince Tsai-Tao of China, in the course of a speech he delivered at the twelfth annual dinner of the American Asiatic Association at Delmonico's last night, said that the thirst for foreign knowledge is general throughout the Chinese Empire, and that at the present moment the "old order of things is fast giving place to the new."

headline.main: TSAI TAO PROCLAIMS CHINA'S AWAKENING; Thirst for Foreign Knowledge Is Now General There, He Tells Asiatic Society.
